If you want to say "Hello, World!" in Swift and push it to GitHub, follow these steps.
mkdir Swift-Hello
cd Swift-Hello
Now, write this code in the hello.swift file:
touch hello.swift
print("Hello, World!")
2. Run the program

In the terminal:
swift hello.swift
3. Get started with Git for GitHub.
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Add Swift Hello World"
